{
    "componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-blog-post-js",
    "path": "/blog/reactnativesalesforce",
    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://milenology.com"}},"posts":{"html":"<p>With the rise in modern app development and an increased demand by customers for native ways to allow developers to extend and customize their line-of-business applications, I'm sharing this post to discuss how I have developed a <a href=\"https://reactnative.dev/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">React Native</a> + <a href=\"https://expo.dev/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Expo</a> mobile app using open source tools, while easily extending a set of architecture solution pattern that expands the power of Salesforce Platform and data to developers.</p>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"The-React-Native-Mobile-Clienteling-App\" style=\"position:relative;\">The React Native Mobile Clienteling App<a href=\"#The-React-Native-Mobile-Clienteling-App\" aria-label=\"The React Native Mobile Clienteling App permalink\" class=\"remark-header-anchor after\"><svg id=\"header-anchor-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>This mobile app demo aims to showcase a simple retail (Eureka) clienteling use-case, where in-store associates are empowered to identify their most loyal customers and their preferences, so as to provide a more targeted service to improve sales.</p>\n<p>In this demo app, some clienteling features include the Home Screen which features a sample dashboard performance of the store and associates, a Me - Profile Screen centered around the associate's performance, and most importantly, a Customers Screen for associates to access insights of their loyal customers.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; margin: 0.7rem 0; margin-left: 0!important; margin-right: 0!important;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Eureka App Screenshots\"\n        title=\"Eureka App Screenshots\"\n        src=\"/static/be7fc6818cf5b39bbdd045922dc8de4d/5a190/app-screenshots.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/be7fc6818cf5b39bbdd045922dc8de4d/772e8/app-screenshots.png 200w,\n/static/be7fc6818cf5b39bbdd045922dc8de4d/e17e5/app-screenshots.png 400w,\n/static/be7fc6818cf5b39bbdd045922dc8de4d/5a190/app-screenshots.png 800w,\n/static/be7fc6818cf5b39bbdd045922dc8de4d/c1b63/app-screenshots.png 1200w,\n/static/be7fc6818cf5b39bbdd045922dc8de4d/29007/app-screenshots.png 1600w,\n/static/be7fc6818cf5b39bbdd045922dc8de4d/63908/app-screenshots.png 2410w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>In this blog, I'll focus more on how I can easily interact with Salesforce data via the mobile app. For the purpose of this demo, I have created a custom object in Salesforce called Eureka Customers, and I want to enable the mobile app to interact with the data securely and at scale.</p>\n<p>For interested developers, the full source code of the React Native sample mobile app is available on Github (note that it is still work in progress).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/terlim-sfdc/eureka\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/terlim-sfdc/eureka</a></p>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"High-level-Architecture\" style=\"position:relative;\">High-level Architecture<a href=\"#High-level-Architecture\" aria-label=\"High level Architecture permalink\" class=\"remark-header-anchor after\"><svg id=\"header-anchor-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>To start off, here is the high-level architecture:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#herokuconnect\">Heroku Connect</a>, which synchronizes data two ways between the Salesforce organization (Eureka Customer Custom Object) and the Heroku Postgres database</li>\n<li><a href=\"#apilayer\">A Heroku App</a> (ExpressJS) is built which serves as the API interface for interacting with the data in the Postgres Database</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"#mobileapp\">Eureka Mobile App</a> uses Axios library to send and retrieve data from the Postgres Database via the Heroku App.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; margin: 0.7rem 0; margin-left: 0!important; margin-right: 0!important;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 46.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Salesforce Architecture\"\n        title=\"Salesforce Architecture\"\n        src=\"/static/d2690b1043f9e6290a88c6d083b1fda6/5a190/architecture.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d2690b1043f9e6290a88c6d083b1fda6/772e8/architecture.png 200w,\n/static/d2690b1043f9e6290a88c6d083b1fda6/e17e5/architecture.png 400w,\n/static/d2690b1043f9e6290a88c6d083b1fda6/5a190/architecture.png 800w,\n/static/d2690b1043f9e6290a88c6d083b1fda6/c1b63/architecture.png 1200w,\n/static/d2690b1043f9e6290a88c6d083b1fda6/29007/architecture.png 1600w,\n/static/d2690b1043f9e6290a88c6d083b1fda6/89557/architecture.png 1928w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><a name=\"herokuconnect\"></a></p>\n<h2 id=\"Connecting-to-Salesforce-CRM-Data-using-Heroku-Connect\" style=\"position:relative;\">Connecting to Salesforce CRM Data using Heroku Connect<a href=\"#Connecting-to-Salesforce-CRM-Data-using-Heroku-Connect\" aria-label=\"Connecting to Salesforce CRM Data using Heroku Connect permalink\" class=\"remark-header-anchor after\"><svg id=\"header-anchor-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>In order for the Eureka Mobile App to interact with Salesforce CRM Data (Eureka Customer Custom Object), I used <a href=\"https://www.heroku.com/connect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Heroku Connect</a>, which is an amazing add-on that easily synchronizes data between a Salesforce organization and a Heroku Postgres database. As you see in the screenshot below, I was able to easily create a mapping of the fields and records of the Eureka Customers object to a table in Postgres with just clicks!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; margin: 0.7rem 0; margin-left: 0!important; margin-right: 0!important;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.49999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Heroku Connect Mapping\"\n        title=\"Heroku Connect Mapping\"\n        src=\"/static/0db983dccfefa84723e35bd51830c199/5a190/heroku-connect.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0db983dccfefa84723e35bd51830c199/772e8/heroku-connect.png 200w,\n/static/0db983dccfefa84723e35bd51830c199/e17e5/heroku-connect.png 400w,\n/static/0db983dccfefa84723e35bd51830c199/5a190/heroku-connect.png 800w,\n/static/0db983dccfefa84723e35bd51830c199/c1b63/heroku-connect.png 1200w,\n/static/0db983dccfefa84723e35bd51830c199/29007/heroku-connect.png 1600w,\n/static/0db983dccfefa84723e35bd51830c199/9b417/heroku-connect.png 2409w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; margin: 0.7rem 0; margin-left: 0!important; margin-right: 0!important;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 24%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Salesforce Eureka Customer Object\"\n        title=\"Salesforce Eureka Customer Object\"\n        src=\"/static/016e811a642c512f81558c32a6fb9208/5a190/salesforce-eureka-customer-obj.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/016e811a642c512f81558c32a6fb9208/772e8/salesforce-eureka-customer-obj.png 200w,\n/static/016e811a642c512f81558c32a6fb9208/e17e5/salesforce-eureka-customer-obj.png 400w,\n/static/016e811a642c512f81558c32a6fb9208/5a190/salesforce-eureka-customer-obj.png 800w,\n/static/016e811a642c512f81558c32a6fb9208/c1b63/salesforce-eureka-customer-obj.png 1200w,\n/static/016e811a642c512f81558c32a6fb9208/29007/salesforce-eureka-customer-obj.png 1600w,\n/static/016e811a642c512f81558c32a6fb9208/ffb95/salesforce-eureka-customer-obj.png 2487w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<br />\n<p><a name=\"apilayer\"></a></p>\n<h2 id=\"The-API-interface-layer-on-Heroku\" style=\"position:relative;\">The API interface layer on Heroku<a href=\"#The-API-interface-layer-on-Heroku\" aria-label=\"The API interface layer on Heroku permalink\" class=\"remark-header-anchor after\"><svg id=\"header-anchor-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Once the mapping of the Salesforce CRM is completed and replicated on a Postgres database in Heroku, the next step involves creating an API interface layer to handle the API requests from the mobile app (or in fact any other apps). I used <a href=\"https://expressjs.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">ExpressJS</a> to create this middleware layer to be utilized by the mobile app. This is actually a very simple web app hosted on Heroku, and I can easily query for the list of all the customer's data as follows using the HTTP GET method:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"20919682109076287000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`app.get('/customers', (req, res) => {\n  client.query('SELECT * FROM salesforce.eureka_customers__c;', (err, result) => {\n    if (err) throw err;\n    for (let row of result.rows) {\n      console.log(JSON.stringify(row));\n    }\n    res.send(result.rows);\n  });\n});`, `20919682109076287000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-javascript line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">app<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'/customers'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">req<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> res</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  client<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">query</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'SELECT * FROM salesforce.eureka_customers__c;'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">err<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> result</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>err<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">throw</span> err<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> row <span class=\"token keyword\">of</span> result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>rows<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">stringify</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>row<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    res<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">send</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>rows<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Alternatively, I can also create routes using paths to easily query for each customer using their Customer ID, which is very useful within the Customer Details Screen:</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"41312585679882490000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`app.get('/customers/:userId', (req, res) => {\n  const userId = req.params.userId;\n  client.query(\n    'SELECT * FROM salesforce.eureka_customers__c WHERE id = \\$1;',\n    [userId],\n    (err, result) => {\n      if (err) throw err;\n      for (let row of result.rows) {\n        console.log(JSON.stringify(row));\n      }\n      res.send(result.rows);\n    }\n  );\n});`, `41312585679882490000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-javascript line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">app<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'/customers/:userId'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">req<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> res</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> userId <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> req<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>params<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>userId<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  client<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">query</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">'SELECT * FROM salesforce.eureka_customers__c WHERE id = $1;'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>userId<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">err<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> result</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>err<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">throw</span> err<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> row <span class=\"token keyword\">of</span> result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>rows<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">stringify</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>row<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      res<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">send</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>rows<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Finally, to allow the mobile app to modify existing data using the HTTP POST method, the following code allows me to update the Postgres database via an API call. Once the Postgres database is updated, Heroku Connect magically synchronizes the Eureka Customer Object in Salesforce.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"78465897802418930000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`app.post('/customers', (req, res) => {\n  const { id, name, email, address, phone } = req.body;\n  client.query(\n    'UPDATE salesforce.eureka_customers__c SET name__c = \\$2, email__c = \\$3, address__c = \\$4, phone__c = \\$5 WHERE id = \\$1;',\n    [id, name, email, address, phone],\n    (err, result) => {\n      if (err) throw err;\n      for (let row of result.rows) {\n        console.log(JSON.stringify(row));\n      }\n      res.send(\\`User modified with ID: \\${id}\\`);\n    }\n  );\n});`, `78465897802418930000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-javascript line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">app<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">post</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'/customers'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">req<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> res</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> id<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> name<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> email<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> address<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> phone <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> req<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>body<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  client<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">query</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">'UPDATE salesforce.eureka_customers__c SET name__c = $2, email__c = $3, address__c = $4, phone__c = $5 WHERE id = $1;'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>id<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> name<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> email<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> address<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> phone<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">err<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> result</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>err<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">throw</span> err<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> row <span class=\"token keyword\">of</span> result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>rows<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">stringify</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>row<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      res<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">send</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">User modified with ID: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>id<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>In a typical production implementation, it would definitely be good practice to implement a security feature to ensure the right authentication exists in the header of the API requests, to allow only authenticated apps to access or make changes to the Postgres database and the Salesforce organization. For the purpose of this demo, this security feature wasn't implemented.</p>\n<p>For interested developers, you may view the full source code of this ExpressJS API interface app on Github:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/terlim-sfdc/eureka-server/blob/master/app.js\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/terlim-sfdc/eureka-server/blob/master/app.js</a>.</p>\n<br />\n<a name=\"mobileapp\"></a>\n<h2 id=\"Using-Salesforce-Customers-Data-from-the-Mobile-App\" style=\"position:relative;\">Using Salesforce Customers Data from the Mobile App<a href=\"#Using-Salesforce-Customers-Data-from-the-Mobile-App\" aria-label=\"Using Salesforce Customers Data from the Mobile App permalink\" class=\"remark-header-anchor after\"><svg id=\"header-anchor-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Within the React Native Mobile App, Axios Javascript library is used to make the HTTP requests and API calls to the API interface layer app. This a sample code which is used for querying the database content.</p>\n<p>To explain briefly on this sample code below, there is an asynchronous call using Axios to retrieve the customer list from the Postgres database, and <em>setCustomers</em> is used to update the state of the customers data object in the app.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"67527247116058350000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`// Fetch Customers from Database\nconst url = \\`https://eureka-mobile-demo.herokuapp.com/customers\\`;\nconst fetchCustomers = async () => {\n  try {\n    setIsLoading(true);\n    const response = await axios.get(url);\n    if (response.status === 200) {\n      setCustomers(response.data);\n      setIsLoading(false);\n      return;\n    } else {\n      throw new Error('Failed to fetch customers from data');\n    }\n  } catch (error) {\n    if (axios.isCancel(error)) {\n      console.log('Customer Data fetching cancelled');\n    } else {\n      console.log(error);\n      setIsLoading(false);\n    }\n  }\n};`, `67527247116058350000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-javascript line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Fetch Customers from Database</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> url <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">https://eureka-mobile-demo.herokuapp.com/customers</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">fetchCustomers</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">try</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setIsLoading</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> response <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> axios<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>url<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>response<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>status <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token number\">200</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token function\">setCustomers</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>response<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token function\">setIsLoading</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">throw</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Error</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Failed to fetch customers from data'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">catch</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>error<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>axios<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">isCancel</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>error<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Customer Data fetching cancelled'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>error<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n      <span class=\"token function\">setIsLoading</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Having implemented the feature to query the API via a GET method above, it is reasonable to also have a functionality to call the POST method to modify the content of the Postgres database. This eventually also updates the Eureka Customers Custom object within the Salesforce tenant/organization using Heroku Connect.</p>\n<p>Here is a sample code of how the Update Customer Details Screen is implemented by calling the <em>handleSubmit</em> method when the Customer Details Update form is submitted within the app, which sends the updated <em>customerDataObject</em> from the state of the app to the Heroku ExpressJS App.</p>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"16345373441056310000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3000\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`const baseURL = \\`https://eureka-mobile-demo.herokuapp.com/customers\\`;\nconst handleSubmit = () => {\n  var data = qs.stringify(customerDataObject);\n  var config = {\n    method: 'post',\n    url: baseURL,\n    headers: {\n      'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'\n    },\n    data: data\n  };\n\n  axios(config)\n    .then(function (response) {\n      console.log(JSON.stringify(response.data));\n    })\n    .catch(function (error) {\n      console.log(error);\n    });\n  Alert.alert('Customer details updated!');\n};`, `16345373441056310000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-javascript line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> baseURL <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">https://eureka-mobile-demo.herokuapp.com/customers</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleSubmit</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> data <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> qs<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">stringify</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>customerDataObject<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> config <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    method<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'post'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    url<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> baseURL<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    headers<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token string\">'Content-Type'</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    data<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> data\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token function\">axios</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>config<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">response</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token constant\">JSON</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">stringify</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>response<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">catch</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">error</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>error<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  Alert<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Customer details updated!'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>For interested developers, you may check out the full source code of the React Native sample mobile app on Github (note that it is still work in progress).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/terlim-sfdc/eureka\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/terlim-sfdc/eureka</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"Summary\" style=\"position:relative;\">Summary<a href=\"#Summary\" aria-label=\"Summary permalink\" class=\"remark-header-anchor after\"><svg id=\"header-anchor-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>With the power of the Salesforce platform, Salesforce customers can easily build any custom app - be is a web app or a mobile app as per this blog/demo, while easily having the flexibility to access the 360 view of their customers within the Salesforce CRM. This is made extremely secure and efficient with Heroku as a Platform as a Service (PaaS), as well as Heroku Connect to provide that magic for any custom app to easily access Salesforce data.</p>","excerpt":"With the rise in modern app development and an increased demand by customers for native ways to allow developers to extend and customize their line-of-business applications, I'm sharing this post to discuss how I have developed a React Native + Expo…","fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"7 min read"}},"frontmatter":{"date":"02 January, 2022","slug":"reactnativesalesforce","title":"Building React Native with Salesforce","tags":["technology","salesforce"],"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"backgroundColor":"transparent","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/8772851cf1f98e051dfa0a7a734aa660/6fc77/react-native-salesforce.png","srcSet":"/static/8772851cf1f98e051dfa0a7a734aa660/85ced/react-native-salesforce.png 800w,\n/static/8772851cf1f98e051dfa0a7a734aa660/7c498/react-native-salesforce.png 1080w,\n/static/8772851cf1f98e051dfa0a7a734aa660/6fc77/react-native-salesforce.png 1200w","sizes":"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/8772851cf1f98e051dfa0a7a734aa660/28281/react-native-salesforce.webp 800w,\n/static/8772851cf1f98e051dfa0a7a734aa660/0b5d5/react-native-salesforce.webp 1080w,\n/static/8772851cf1f98e051dfa0a7a734aa660/a020d/react-native-salesforce.webp 1200w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 1200px) 1200px, 100vw"}]},"width":1200,"height":500}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"reactnativesalesforce"}},
